WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.797 --> 00:00:13.917
 Circular Embroider No. 83 can sew impressive circular decorative stitches. 

00:00:14.871 --> 00:00:21.791
 Contains a round embroidery machine, 2 mounting screws and a special screwdriver. 

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:28.860
 Make a circular pattern by making decorative sewing circular. 

00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:40.140
 Attach the No. 20 C open embroidery presser and let the sewing machine recognize the presser (varies depending on the model). 

00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:49.860
 Set round embroidery machine. 

00:00:51.120 --> 00:01:01.060
 Set the screw hole on the end of the embroidery machine to the right and set it, and screw the left screw hole on the free arm. 

00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:09.160
 The movable position pin is at the center of the circle, and can be moved to the left or right to make a circle of different size. 

00:01:09.940 --> 00:01:20.100
 Take the rubber cap. The pin comes out, so stick the dough there and cover the rubber cap. 

00:01:25.448 --> 00:01:30.368
 It is recommended to use a stable paper to prevent the fabric from getting wrinkled. 

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:43.280
 Select decorative sewing. For example, select No. 407, the swing width is set to maximum, the feed is set to 0.3, and the needle base line is set to the center. The needle position at the end of sewing is at the bottom. 

00:01:44.060 --> 00:01:48.260
 Change the pattern length and density according to your preference. 

00:01:49.060 --> 00:01:54.660
 Please move the pin together with the fabric and move it to the desired position. 

00:01:56.120 --> 00:02:01.340
 Lower the presser and start sewing from the beginning of the decorative sewing pattern. 

00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:08.660
 Stop once at about the third pattern before the end of sewing. 

00:02:09.671 --> 00:02:16.611
 Adjust by stretching or packing the pattern so that the last pattern matches the beginning of the first pattern. 

00:02:17.140 --> 00:02:24.200
 Stop the end of sewing by pressing the single pattern sewing button or the sewing button. Cut the thread and raise the presser. 

00:02:28.060 --> 00:02:31.640
 Move the pin to a new position. 

00:02:33.963 --> 00:02:40.523
 Select a new decorative sewing, this time select No. 603. 

00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:47.090
 Lower the presser and sew a new pattern. 

00:02:54.178 --> 00:03:02.318
 You can bring amazing effects to your work with mirror work, pattern length changes, stitch combinations, and more. 

00:03:03.520 --> 00:03:08.880
 You can also make round appliques. 

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:15.980
 First sew in a straight line and round, and then finish around with satin stitching. 

00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:22.180
 You can sew using other pressers. For example, you can make an applique border with No. 21 Braiding Press. 

00:03:22.960 --> 00:03:29.860
 Circular embroidery devices can also be attached to the right side of the presser. Because the direction of the pattern can be changed, it is especially effective for decorative sewing such as alphabets. 

